BC</a> reported.Gooden was the NL Rookie of the Year in 1984 and helped the Mets win the World Series in 1986. In 1996, he pitched a no-hitter for the New York Yankees. He had a <a href="https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/g/goodedw01.shtml" target="_blank">career record</a> of 197-112 with a 3.51 ERA.Gooden is due in Newark Municipal Court on July 30 to answer his latest charges, <a href="https://www.nj.com/yankees/2019/07/ex-yankees-mets-pitcher-dwight-gooden-arrested-again-whats-he-accused-of-doing-this-time.html" target="_blank">NJ.com</a> reported.<a href="/weather/interactive-radar" target="_top">Interactive Radar</a><br />
